condition.narrative: Adopt regulations to enforce Coastal Infrastructure Management Plans, adopted by the borrower
Adoption of Codes of Environmental Practice are in progress
Adoption of EIA regulations are in progress
Establish an environmental compliance monitoring system
Monitor natural hazards zones and changes in baseline conditions; publish results every 3 years
Prepare time-bound action plan to implement transport sector reform; carry out plan
Samoa Airport Authority to maintain corporate business plan; review its financial performance and submit report to IDA no laterthan Nov 30 of each year, starting 2004
The Recipient shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Anti-Corruption Guidelines
The Recipient shall have the financial statements audited each fiscal year and shall furnish the audited Financial Statements toIDA not later than six months after the end of each fiscal year
The Recipient shall maintain a financial management system acceptable to IDA
The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the project and prepare Quarterly Project Reports which shall befurnishedto IDA not later than 45 days after the reporting period end
